# Cursor MCP — portable config (no reload after pull)

[.cursor/mcp.json](../../.cursor/mcp.json) is **fully tracked** and uses **repo-relative bash wrappers** (`scripts/cursor-mcp-*.sh`, `scripts/start-brv-mcp.sh`). No machine-specific absolute paths.

## After `git pull`

- **Do not** run `npm run cursor-mcp:config` routinely.
- **Do not** reload Cursor MCP unless `.cursor/mcp.json` or wrapper scripts **changed** in the pull.
- **Do** run `npm run build` when `src/` or TypeScript deps changed (wrappers need `dist/`).

## When to regenerate or reload (rare)

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| First clone / new machine | `npm install` · `npm run setup-mcp-prereqs` · `npm run build` · enable project MCP once |
| `.cursor/mcp.json` or `scripts/cursor-mcp-*.sh` changed on pull | One-time Cursor MCP Reload |
| Windows Cursor host, repo in WSL | `npm run cursor-mcp:config -- --variant windows-wsl` once per host |

Details: [CURSOR_MCP_TEMPLATE.md](../../docs/CURSOR_MCP_TEMPLATE.md)
